The paper deals with a communication system for Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT), which involves wireless communication and networked systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also discusses the design framework for the IIoT system, which involves networked systems and communication protocols, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper also discusses the system's performance, which involves control and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. The paper also discusses the use of massive SIMO systems, which involves signal processing and machine learning, making cs.MM (Machine Learning) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of noncoherent maximum-likelihood detectors, which involves communication theory and protocols, making cs.COM (Computers and Society) another possible category.
